runesofwizardry.guidebook.category.basic=Basics
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.general=Dusts, Runes and Inscriptions
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.general.text=Greetings, aspiring wizard. There are three basic things that you should know:\n\nFirst and foremost, dusts. Dusts can be placed in a 4x4 pattern on each block, and identical dust spots will connect together, creating interesting patterns that can be used for decorative purposes.
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.general.text.1=Not much Wizardry in that, is there? This is what brings us to the next element, Runes. Runes are special patterns of dust that can be activated to have an effect on the world, although most of them will also require a sacrifice of some sort, and some may even require to be fueled.
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.general.text.2=Inscriptions are small drawings that can be worn in the chestplate slot or as an amulet (if you have Baubles). They are crafted with special "Inscribing Runes", which are able to transfer their pattern to a piece of parchment. They will then need to be charged (once again with a sacrifice) by the Rune of Inscription Enchanting before they can have any effect.
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.rune_activation=Activating Runes
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.rune_activation.text=Runes are activated with sneak + right-click with an empty hand on a block of placed dust.\n\nThere must be at least 2 blocks between the rune to activate and other dust blocks. Make sure that all dusts are placed, that you have replaced placeholder dusts (if any) and that the appropriate sacrifice is on a dust block.
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.commands=Commands
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.commands.export=/rw_export <name> : \nSaves the pattern you are looking at as a JSON file in \n[minecraft folder]/\nrunesofwizardry_patterns
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.commands.import=/rw_import [runeID|filename] [natural | centered | topleft]:\n\nImports the pattern described by the rune's ID (modid:runeid) or a JSON file in\nrunesofwizardry_patterns and places it in the world.\n\nIf not specified otherwise, the block looked at will be the "natural" alignment of the pattern, (centered or the rune's entity position)
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.pestle.description=To work with dusts, one must first make dust. A pestle of bone and stone should be able to handle that...
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.runic_dictionnary.description=The Enhanced Edition isn't readable, but it allows you to place runes in-world with a simple shift+right-click. The tooltip also has the Rune's details.
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.broom.description=A simple broom will allow you to quickly clear placed dust
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.dust_pouch.description=This pouch can store a nearly infinite amount of a single dust type, automatically collects picked-up dust and can be used to place dust in the world.
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.dust_pouch.description.1=Craft with dust to set type or add to the pouch, craft on its own to take one stack out.
runesofwizardry.guidebook.entry.basic.sacrifice_negator.description=(creative only) Use this instead of the sacrifice required to activate any Rune.

